From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Mon, 7 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +1200
Subject: [PATCH] iommu/rockchip: force GFP_DMA32 for v2 page tables

The RK3566/RK3568 IOMMU v2 hardware cannot fetch a page table located\nabove 4 GB, but iommu_data_ops_v2 left .gfp_flags = 0, so on >4GB boards\nthe NPU IOMMU bus-errors. Set GFP_DMA32 like the v1 ops. This is why the\nout-of-tree module alone cannot enable IOMMU on RK3566/68; a kernel build\ncan. Harmless on SoCs (RK3576/RK3588) whose v2 HW can reach >4GB.

Signed-off-by: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
---
diff --git a/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c b/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c
--- a/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c
+++ b/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c
@@ -1359,7 +1359,13 @@
 	.mk_dtentries = &rk_mk_dte_v2,
 	.mk_ptentries = &rk_mk_pte_v2,
 	.dma_bit_mask = DMA_BIT_MASK(40),
-	.gfp_flags = 0,
+	/*
+	 * The v2 DTE format encodes >32-bit page-table addresses, but the
+	 * RK3566/RK3568 IOMMU v2 hardware cannot actually fetch a page table
+	 * located above 4 GB -- doing so bus-errors the NPU. Force page tables
+	 * into the DMA32 zone like v1. Harmless on SoCs that can reach >4GB.
+	 */
+	.gfp_flags = GFP_DMA32,
 };
 
 static const struct of_device_id rk_iommu_dt_ids[] = {
--
2.43.0
